^ let it be known, Nix is merciful
I always end up softening some edges because I get annoyed by my own stuff while playing
genuinely, Nix’s best strength as a creator is restraint, in my opinion.  he makes hard stuff, but there is always thought  and intentionality throughout

Most of what I do is just ask myself if the effort was worth how interesting or satisfying something felt to do, and of course that would get different results from other players, but it usually steers me toward designs I am fine with.
And the satisfaction of one obstacle is in constant conversation with the adjacent ones
I try to budget around difficulty vs satisfaction, and definitely don't set out trying to make it as awful as possible

also re: one tile gaps being hard in this section.  in both obstacles you are incentivized to be holding jump the whole way down.  in other situations you would normally fast fall through a one tile gap, so here you are exposed for longer if you move too far right or left
